    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. You mentioned blockages being a danger though—what actually causes those? Like, what are the most common things that end up clogging the tube in real-world scenarios?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The most common culprits for clogging a pitot tube are insects, especially larger ones, or accumulated debris like dust and dirt, particularly in dusty environments. Icing is another serious threat, which can freeze onto the opening and effectively block the airflow entirely. Sometimes, bird strikes can physically damage or partially obstruct the tube, so keeping it clear is a constant maintenance necessity.",
      "source": "target",
